Package: nilHMM
Title: Duration-Aware HMM Ancestry Caller for NIL Sequencing Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Fausto", "Rodriguez Zapata", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "thegemmalab@ncsu.edu")
Description: A unified R + Rcpp reimplementation of the nilHMM ancestry-calling
    family for Near-Isogenic Lines from sequencing data. A single
    duration-aware 3-state (REF/HET/ALT) HMM engine with swappable emission
    models (count / gt) and duration layers (geometric / rigidity / hsmm)
    expresses the nnil and rtiger callers, alongside the binhmm bin/cluster
    caller. The package is data-agnostic: functions take (data, params) and
    return calls; pipeline scripts own paths and sample lists. See
    REFACTOR_R_PACKAGE.md.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1)
LinkingTo:
    Rcpp,
    RcppParallel
Imports:
    Rcpp,
    RcppParallel,
    stats,
    parallel,
    utils
SystemRequirements: GNU make
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    GenomicRanges,
    rebmix
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
